voices.mp3Text: Time and Tidehunter wait for no man.
Time and Tidehunter wait for no man.
Let's catch this tide and catch them in it.
We'll turn this tide to our advantage.
You can't hide from the tide.
I'm hungry enough to eat a plankton.
I could eat a sea cucumber.
I'm so hungry I could eat a mackerel.
I could eat a giant isopod.
Ha ha! I could eat a walrus.
I'm hungry enough to eat a manta ray.
I could eat a whale shark.
I could eat a blue whale.
I could eat a colossal squid.
I hang a coral wreath on your grave.
I pull you to the bottom.
I bring sad tidings: You're dead!
Ha ha ha ha ha ha, Now you're fish food.
Ha ha ha! Women and children and Kunkka first.
The admirable Admiral dies like a dog!
voices.name: Kunkka

voices.mp3Text: The admirable Kunkka dies like a dog!
voices.name: Kunkka

voices.mp3Text: I always pitied you, Morphling, for having to carry Kunkka's ships.
voices.name: Morphling

voices.mp3Text: Alas poor Morphling, so full of tasty fish.
voices.name: Morphling

voices.mp3Text: Ah, sweet Siren, if only you'd steered Kunkka onto the rocks.
voices.name: Naga Siren

voices.mp3Text: You should put your fire to work burning up Kunkka's ships.
voices.name: Lina

voices.mp3Text: Why fire your arrows at me when Kunkka's sails need burning?
voices.name: Clinkz

voices.mp3Text: Why fight me, Slardar? Together we could have brought Kunkka to the bottom.
voices.name: Slardar

voices.mp3Text: You could have given Kunkka some pointers in how to die nobly.
voices.name: Lycan

voices.mp3Text: You were a commanding presence, which is more than I can say for Kunkka.
voices.name: Sand King

voices.mp3Text: Puck, you taste as bad as Kunkka's boot!
voices.name: Puck

voices.mp3Text: Take a bath, Axe. You smell worse than Kunkka!
voices.name: Axe

voices.mp3Text: Your metal jacket sank you faster than one of Kunkka's ships.
voices.name: Clockwerk

voices.mp3Text: You went down like Kunkka's ship.
voices.name: Tiny

voices.mp3Text: Next time, Weaver, let Kunkka give you lessons in scuttling.
voices.name: Weaver

voices.mp3Text: He abandoned this plane faster than Kunkka abandoned his fleet.
voices.name: Enigma

voices.mp3Text: Did you think I'd blunder? You must have mistaken me for Kunkka.
voices.name: Dark Seer

voices.mp3Text: Blood in the water, time to feed!
Kunkka, I thought I left you on the bottom of the sea.
voices.name: Kunkka

voices.mp3Text: Ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha!
Ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha.
Blink dagger, for a quick stab in the dark.
voices.name: Blink Dagger (2250)

voices.mp3Text: This will put a blink in my step!
voices.name: Blink Dagger (2250)

voices.mp3Text: And so it falls to me.
voices.name: Aghanim's Scepter (4200)

voices.mp3Text: Let the sharks have my flesh!
My body, cast upon the tides.
I'll have my vengeance yet, Kunkka!
voices.name: Kunkka

voices.mp3Text: I rise again from the deeps.
Fresh is good…unless we're talking water.
Got to keep moving, or I suffocate.
Look what the tide washed in.
Ha ha ha! A rogue wave carries me back!
If I could catch tide in a bottle…
These tidepool reflections dazzle the eye.
Seen enough of me, have you?
Nothing wrong with a few extra growths.

text: Third and more attempts within 10 seconds
Third and more attempts within 10 seconds

voices.mp3Text: Who needs a big brain when you've got teeth like mine?
By Maelrawn the Tentacular, the Lurker in the Whirlpool, may my enemies be sucked down in spirals!
Leave the depths to the treacherous Meranths, I can find all I need in the shallows.
